Package: blockr.dm
Title: Relational Data Management Blocks for 'blockr'
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R:
    c(person(given = "Christoph",
             family = "Sax",
             role = c("aut", "cre"),
             email = "christoph@cynkra.com"))
Maintainer: Christoph Sax <christoph@cynkra.com>
Description: Extends 'blockr.core' with interactive blocks for visual management
    of relational data using the 'dm' package. Users can combine multiple data
    frames into data models, define primary and foreign key relationships,
    filter across related tables with automatic cascading, and flatten to single
    tables. Includes interactive diagrams showing table relationships.
    Particularly useful for pharmaceutical data like ADaM datasets where tables
    share subject identifiers (USUBJID).
